## Summary
Implement `PagServer.Commands.Parser` to parse raw text input into command name + args.

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] `parse/1` accepts a string, returns `{:command, name, args}` or `:not_a_command`
- [ ] Detects leading slash: "/model gpt-4o" -> {:command, "model", ["gpt-4o"]}
- [ ] Text with no leading slash returns `:not_a_command`
- [ ] Handles empty args: "/help" -> {:command, "help", []}
- [ ] Trims whitespace, handles multiple spaces between args
- [ ] First word after slash is the command name (lowercased)
- [ ] Remaining words are individual args (not joined — let handlers decide)
- [ ] "/" alone returns `:not_a_command`
- [ ] Tests cover all above cases


